Packers Stay Undefeated; Falcons, Steelers and Bengals Win NFL Early Games

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-10-16T20:05:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/packers-stay-undefeated-falcons-steelers-and-bengals-win-nfl-early-games.html
Aaron Rodgers  had three second-
quarter touchdown passes and the Green Bay Packers remained
undefeated with a 24-3 victory at home against the winless  St.
Louis Rams .  Rodgers was 17-of-28 for 310 yards, including a 93-yard
scoring pass to Jordy Nelson, as the defending Super Bowl
champions improved to 6-0. Sam Bradford went 28-of-44 for 321
yards for the Rams, who fell to 0-5.  In other early National Football League games today, the
Atlanta Falcons (3-3) scored 17 unanswered fourth-quarter points
to defeat the visiting Carolina Panthers 31-17. Cam Newton threw
for 237 yards and had a 14-yard touchdown run for Carolina (1-5)
and was intercepted three times.  Andy Dalton threw for 264 yards to lead the host  Cincinnati
Bengals  (4-2) to a 27-17 victory against the winless
Indianapolis Colts. The Pittsburgh Steelers (4-2) won 17-13 at
home against the Jacksonville Jaguars (1-5).  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  